result.execSummary:
The defendant Ray A Munoz Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child (At Least 3 Violations of 1st or 2nd Degree Sexual Assault), a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.025(1)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Length of confinement and length of extended supervision for a total length of 18 years bifurcated sentence.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law.  Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations.  If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
Obtain GED or full time employment equal to 40 hours per week.

No contact with the victim (person, property, residence or family).  No contact with any individual under the age of 18 unless approved by agent and their parent.  Counseling, treatment, services as deemed appropriate by agent, including Sex Offender Treatment. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations of probation.  Defendant must register with the Sex Offender Registry and comply with all rules and requirements of the Sex Offender Registry.  Firearm warning given.  Voting prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored.
